Celebi, Koza Altin, Sinpas: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-25T07:45:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/celebi-koza-altin-sinpas-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  rose 636.22, or 1
percent, to 64,355.86 yesterday.  Celebi Hava Servisi AS (CLEBI)  : The Turkish airport
services company bid for the rights to operate Brussels National
Airport’s ground handling services for seven years, it said in a
statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange after the market closed
yesterday. Celebi climbed 65 kurus, or 2.6 percent, to 25.25
liras.  Dogan Yayin Holding AS (DYHOL)  : Turkey’s biggest media
group said the country’s top administrative court approved a
lower court ruling in favor of its unit Dogan Produksiyon
Hizmetleri AS in a case concerning a payment order for 862.9
million liras ($557 million) in backtaxes and fines from 2006,
according to a statement to the bourse today. Dogan Yayin gained
3 kurus, or 1.5 percent, to 2 liras.  Koza Altin Isletmeleri AS (KOZAL)  : The Turkish gold
miner’s owners Koza-Ipek Holding AS, ATP Insaat & Ticaret AS,
Koza Anadolu Metal Madencilik Isletmeleri AS and Ipek
Matbaacilik Sanayi & Ticaret AS will sell up to 16.8 million
shares in the company, Koza Altin said in a statement to the
bourse after the market closed yesterday. Koza Altin advanced 40
kurus, or 1.9 percent, to 21.75 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin  in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
